BFN 

  [Text] Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis, Lithuanian 
President Algirdas Brazauskas, and Estonian President Lennart 
Meri will meet at Jurmala resort near Riga on 3 May. According 
to the presidential office, the meeting, held at Guntis Ulmanis' 
initiative, will be private. 
  Lennart Meri, Algirdas Brazauskas, and Guntis Ulmanis are 
expected to discuss confidentially problems linked to the 
withdrawal of the Russian Army from Latvia and Estonia. The 
presidents also may adopt a joint statement on this issue. A 
news conference on the outcome of the meeting is not scheduled. 

